  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Asst Accounts Executive",
  "description": "<p>Established since 1937, the Ong Radio Group is amongst Asia Pacific’s foremost in luxury residential entertainment systems, consultancy and design.</p><p>The group represents many of the world’s premier and niche brands, with a clientele consisting mainly of the region’s crème de la crème.</p><p>Its primary businesses in Singapore include luxury retailing, turn-key project management, system specialist consulting and brand distribution.</p><p><strong>Job Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li>Perform month-end and year-end closing activities for group of companies;</li><li>Handling partial set of accounts;</li><li>Prepare and submit GST returns;</li><li>Monitor and post all incoming payments to customer accounts;</li><li>Prepare monthly debtors reconciliation and statement of accounts;</li><li>Manage accounts receivables functions include veifying supplier invoices, initiating payment, data entry, AR aging and report;</li><li>Maintenance and reconciliation of creditor/debtor ledger;</li><li>Accounting/bookkeeping duties;</li><li>Enter accurate data into the accounting system;</li><li>Retrieve system reports from the accounting system for management’s use;</li><li>Liaise with external accounting firm as assigned;</li><li>Prepare and submit claims such NS claims, grants and other;</li><li>Ensure proper filing of accounting documents;</li><li>Undertake such other work as may be assigned from time to time.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications and Skills:</strong></p><ul><li>At least Nitec in Accounting or a related field</li><li>Proficient in Microsoft Office and accounting systems</li><li>Min. 3 years of experience in an accounting role</li><li>Able to work with minimum supervision</li></ul><p>Willing to work at Changi South area. We offer 5-day work week, good career advancement, birthday leave and many more staff benefits. Only shortlisted candidates will be notified. Salary nego.</p>",
